@palladin9479 There was a "home invasion" burglary (theft of alcohol) in Vermont.  Miller entered the unlocked residence without permission.  He was charged with Felony Burglary, Unlawful Trespass and Petit Larceny, and was facing up to 26 years imprisonment.  It was plead down to only the Unlawful Trespass charge, where he received a 90 day suspended jail sentence, 1 year probation and a $250 fine

Also around the same time in Vermont there was an issue at Miller's Vermont farmhouse, where a mother and 3 children were also living, in reportedly chaotic conditions, with loose ammunition and firearms scattered about and easily accessible.  Multiple sources described Miller's farm as an "unlicensed cannabis operation".  No charges were laid against Miller over any of it and none of the allegations were ever tested in court.

Most of the allegations regarding the firearms and cannabis came from mainstream magazine and radio reporting, originating from the father of the children after he had visited the property, and also from 2 independent witnesses of conditions at Miller's farm.

